tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All results are within normal limits except for a mildly elevated creatinine, which may suggest early renal impairment or dehydration. Glucose metabolism and lipid profile are within target ranges. Recommend correlating creatinine with clinical context, reviewing renal function trend, and ensuring adequate hydration. No acute laboratory concerns identified.
